tspan.tspan: Historia Brittōnum: The History of the Britons: A Latin Reader

text.tspan: contains the full, original Latin text of the Historia Brittōnum,
which is a history of the British Isles written around 831 AD,
often attributed to the Welsh monk Nennius. It tells of the Trojan
origins of the British, the arrival of the Anglo-Saxons Hengist and
Horsa, Saint Germanus, King Vortigern, Ambrosius, Arthur, Saint
Patrick, and the marvels found in Britain.
This is a Latin reader intended for beginning and intermediate
students, so every page of Latin text has a full glossary on the
facing page. Extensive footnotes explaining any difficult grammar
or concepts are included with the original Latin text. The text is
highly legible (it is not photocopied) and has macrons.
